 Here's a JavaScript program that generates and prints the ASCII characters and their corresponding hexadecimal codes for each character from 0 to 7F:

```javascript
for (let i = 32; i <= 126; i++) {
    let charCode = String.fromCharCode(i);
    let hexCode = `0x${i.toString(16)}`.toUpperCase();

    console.log(`Character: ${charCode}, Hex Code: ${hexCode}`);
}
```

This program uses a for loop to iterate through the characters from 32 (space) to 126 (~). It then converts each integer value into its corresponding character using `String.fromCharCode()` and hexadecimal representation using `toString(16)`. Finally, it prints out the character along with its hexadecimal code.
